div.span: token wait duration: flow control for all commands in TiDB, it's extremely fast when there are enough tokens in the pool.

parse duration: parse sql statement to AST. For simplicity, we assume 1 command contains 1 sql only.
retry duration: some queries may suffer from failure and they are retryable(due to both logical and system failures), if the retry is successful, the failure duration will be part of latency.
compile duration: optimize query and compile it to physical plan is required.
execution duration: this phase contains writing result to the client, and there are many different possible paths, it's significantly different for read/write queries.
